title: W-MU boys finish third at SEISC cross country meet
text:
W-MU boys finish third at SEISC cross country meet Oct 09, 2015 Photo by: Dana Royer Winfield-Mt. Union’s Kohlton Heinzel (38th, 19:36) 
BY ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
COLUMBUS — Henry County’s cross country teams were in action at the Southeast Iowa Super Conference meet in Columbus on Thursday night. 
The Winfield-Mt. Union boys had the best day, finishing third behind first-place Pekin and second-place Wapello. W-MU finished seventh in the girls’ event, which Pekin also won. 
Neither WACO team had enough runners to qualify. The Danville team that includes New London’s runners finished fifth in the girls’ race and eighth in the boys’ race. 
Gavin Bencze led the W-MU boys with a fifth place finish. Bencze ran 17:09 in the race, which was won by Keiffer Sexton of Highland. Johnathon Quinn finished closely behind Bencze with an eighth-place 17:14. 
Drake Mehaffy ran the race in 19:03 for 26th place. Kohlton Heinzel placed 38th, in 19:36. Nick Davis ran in 57th place, in 20:44; Ross Vantiger was 66th, in 21:05; and Kane Harris finished 79th, in 21:56. 
Cecelia Hemsworth placed 21st, in 23:40, to lead the W-MU girls. Whitney Vantiger ran 40th, in 25:57. Isabella Mertens and Kimberlee Warnstaff ran 48th and 49th, in 27:13 and 27:30 respectively. Fionna Sparrow rounded out the Lady Wolves with a 58th place 28:52. The girls’ race was won by Gwynne Wright of Pekin. 
Joe Edeker had the best time for the WACO boys. Edeker finished 83rd, in 22:50. Kiefer Roman finished 89th, in 24:03. Trevor Patagos was 92nd, in 27:49, and Zachariah Parsons placed 96th, in 36:13. 
The WACO girls were led by Cheyenne Sedlacek, who finished in 24:32 for 29th place. Michaela Shaffer was 51st, in 27:47, and Emily Thompson rounded out the Warrior girls with a 31:43 for 65th place.
